The paper deals with the problem of weakly supervised semantic segmentation, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed approach involves the use of attention maps and saliency detection, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also evaluates its approach on the PASCAL VOC12 dataset, which is a popular benchmark in multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) research.
